Enjoy this nice little bit of Icelandic/Viking ultraviolence.  The first of a trilogy that didn't end up nearly as well as it started. (disclosure, I didn't see the final cut of the the third film, just a preview). It really showed the promise of starting a fresh new genre.

Plenty of extras, and trailers from the trilogy.


If you'd like to buy the dvd, here is a link: http://www.simnet.is/hrafng/DVD%20Hrafninn/instructionsHowTobuyDVD.htm

they say that they will release the rest of the trilogy, but it doesn't seem to have happened over the years.  Post them if you get them. They'd be well appreciated.

Thanks to the original uploader!

